                            <comment id="17099332" author="jensg" created="Mon, 4 May 2020 20:26:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t contribute much on the technical aspects but I want to emphasize that a union &lt;b&gt;by definition&lt;/b&gt; has &quot;all optional fields&quot;, otherwise it would not  be a &lt;tt&gt;union&lt;/tt&gt; but a &lt;tt&gt;struct&lt;/tt&gt;. That&apos;s why the compiler complains when you try to set union members to anything else than optional.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
